PMT is a real estate investment trust that invests primarily in residential mortgage 
loans and mortgage-related assets. PMT is externally managed by PennyMac Financial 
Services, Inc. (NYSE: PFSI) through a management agreement with PFSI’s investment 
management subsidiary, PNMAC Capital Management, LLC (PCM). PCM, which is an SEC-registered 
investment advisor specializing in residential mortgage loans, provides PMT with 
management oversight and investment expertise. PMT also maintains loan servicing 
and mortgage banking services agreements with PFSI’s mortgage banking subsidiary, 
PennyMac Loan Services, LLC (PLS). PLS provides primary loan servicing and specialty 
loan servicing for PMT’s portfolio of residential mortgage loans. The servicing 
functions provided by PLS include collecting principal and interest payments, escrow 
account management, customer service, online account access, loss mitigation, collection 
activities, loan workouts, modifications, foreclosures, short sales, refinancing, 
and mortgage financing to facilitate sales of real estate owned properties. PLS 
also performs fulfillment activities for PMT’s correspondent aggregation business, 
including reviews of loan data; documentation and appraisals to assess loan quality 
and risk; correspondent seller performance and credit monitoring procedures; and 
the subsequent sale and securitization of loans through secondary mortgage markets 
on behalf of PMT. Our business model and relationship with PFSI combine the expertise, 
infrastructure, and capital required to invest in the many opportunities available 
in the U.S. mortgage market.









